{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_13","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/zsh -lc \"python3 - <<'PY'\nimport re\nfrom pathlib import Path\ntext=Path('MASTER_TASKS.md').read_text().splitlines()\nfor line in text:\n    m=re.match(r'\"'^- '\"\\\\[( |x)\\\\] IQ-(\\\\d+) (.*)\"'$'\"',line)\n    if m:\n        chk='done' if m.group(1)=='x' else 'todo'\n        num=int(m.group(2)); desc=m.group(3)\n        if num>=16:\n            print(f'IQ-{num:03d} {chk} :: {desc}')\nPY\"","aggregated_output":"IQ-016 todo :: Draft `docs/GGUF_FORMAT.md` skeleton with sections for header, metadata, tensor info, and alignment rules (WS0-02)\nIQ-017 todo :: Write host-side GGUF header/tensor dump fixture plan in `tests/README.md` for llama.cpp parity checks (WS0-05, WS2-05)\nIQ-018 todo :: Create `tests/README.md` skeleton for llama.cpp parity fixtures (header, metadata, tensor offsets) (WS0-05, WS2-05)\nIQ-019 todo :: Create `src/math/fixedpoint.HC` skeleton with Q16 constants, core type aliases, and TODO stubs for mul/div helpers (WS1-01)\nIQ-020 todo :: Implement Q16 integer exponent range clamp and base constants in `src/math/intexp.HC` (WS1-02)\nIQ-021 todo :: Add host-side Q16 exp parity harness in `tests/test_intexp_q16.py` against `math.exp` samples (WS1-05)\nIQ-022 todo :: Implement GGUF header constants and struct layout notes in `src/gguf/header.HC` before parser logic (WS2-01)\nIQ-023 todo :: Create `src/math/rmsnorm.HC` skeleton with Q16 constants, tensor shape assumptions, and TODO stubs for scale/variance accumulation (WS1-04)\nIQ-024 todo :: Create `src/gguf/header.HC` skeleton with `GGUFHeader` struct and endian-safe integer read helper stubs (WS2-01)\nIQ-025 todo :: Add host-side GGUF header parser parity fixture in `tests/test_gguf_header_parse.py` covering valid/magic/version/truncation cases (WS2-01, WS2-05)\nIQ-026 done :: Implement metadata key lookup helpers (`GGUFMetaFindByKey`, scalar extractors) in `src/gguf/metadata.HC` (WS2-02)\nIQ-027 todo :: Add host-side metadata parser parity fixture for scalar/string/array/nested-array cases in `tests/test_gguf_metadata_parse.py` (WS2-02, WS2-05)\nIQ-028 done :: Implement GGUF tensor data base alignment helper in `src/gguf/tensor_data_base.HC` (WS2-04)\nIQ-029 done :: Implement Q8_0 dot product (naive, integer-only accumulator) in `src/quant/q8_0_dot.HC` (WS3-05)\nIQ-030 done :: Implement mixed Q4_0 x Q8_0 dot product kernel in `src/quant/q4_0_q8_0_dot.HC` (WS3-05)\nIQ-031 done :: Implement Q8_0 blockwise dot-to-Q16 accumulation helper in `src/quant/q8_0_dot.HC` for matmul callers (WS4-01)\nIQ-032 todo :: Add mixed Q4_0 x Q8_0 dot parity harness in `tests/test_q4_0_q8_0_dot.py` with GGML-math bounds (WS3-05)\nIQ-033 done :: Implement Q4_0 row-dot helper (`Q4_0DotRowBlocksQ16`) in `src/quant/q4_0_dot.HC` for quant matmul row kernels (WS4-01)\nIQ-034 done :: Implement Q4_0 x Q8_0 blockwise Q16 accumulation helper in `src/quant/q4_0_q8_0_dot.HC` for mixed matmul callers (WS4-01)\nIQ-035 todo :: Add Q8_0 Q16-accumulator parity harness in `tests/test_q8_0_dot_accum_q16.py` with seeded blockwise rounding checks (WS4-01)\nIQ-036 done :: Implement GGUF tensor data offset resolver (`GGUFTensorDataBaseOffset`) in `src/gguf/tensor_data_base.HC` with alignment validation (WS2-04)\nIQ-037 done :: Implement GGML tensor block-size/byte-size helpers in `src/gguf/tensor_data_base.HC` for F32/F16/Q4_0/Q8_0 sizing math (WS2-04)\nIQ-038 done :: Implement GGUF tensor absolute range validator (`GGUFTensorResolveRange`) in `src/gguf/tensor_data_base.HC` with overflow-safe `abs+size` checks (WS2-04)\nIQ-039 todo :: Implement GGUF tensor payload byte-size helper (`GGUFTensorBytesForType`) in `src/gguf/tensor_data_base.HC` for F32/F16/Q4_0/Q8_0 (WS2-04)\nIQ-040 done :: Implement GGUF tensor-table range validator (`GGUFValidateTensorRanges`) in `src/gguf/tensor_data_base.HC` to enforce non-overlap and EOF bounds (WS2-04)\nIQ-041 done :: Implement `GGUFValidateTensorRangesSorted` in `src/gguf/tensor_data_base.HC` using in-place sort + single-pass overlap scan for large tensor tables (WS2-04)\nIQ-042 done :: Implement `GGUFTensorInfoResolveByteSpans` in `src/gguf/tensor_data_base.HC` to derive per-tensor payload bytes from dims+type and feed sorted range validation (WS2-04)\nIQ-043 done :: Implement `GGUFTensorInfoResolveAbsRanges` in `src/gguf/tensor_data_base.HC` to output per-tensor absolute `[start,end)` spans after byte-size derivation and range validation (WS2-04)\nIQ-044 done :: Implement `GGUFTensorRangeFindByAbsOffset` in `src/gguf/tensor_data_base.HC` (binary search over sorted `[start,end)` spans) for O(log n) tensor payload lookup (WS2-04)\nIQ-045 done :: Implement `GGUFTensorRangeFindByRelOffset` in `src/gguf/tensor_data_base.HC` by translating relative offset to absolute and delegating to `GGUFTensorRangeFindByAbsOffset` (WS2-04)\nIQ-046 done :: Implement `GGUFTensorRangeFindByRelOffsetDefault` in `src/gguf/tensor_data_base.HC` using `GGUF_DEFAULT_ALIGNMENT` and delegate to `GGUFTensorRangeFindByRelOffset` (WS2-04)\nIQ-047 done :: Implement `GGUFTensorInfoBuildOffsetIndex` in `src/gguf/tensor_data_base.HC` to build sorted absolute ranges + original tensor indices for stable lookup (WS2-04)\nIQ-048 done :: Add indexed tensor lookup helpers (`GGUFTensorRangeFindIndexByAbsOffset`, `GGUFTensorRangeFindIndexByRelOffset`) in `src/gguf/tensor_data_base.HC` returning original tensor index (WS2-04)\nIQ-049 done :: Add default-alignment indexed lookup helper `GGUFTensorRangeFindIndexByRelOffsetDefault` in `src/gguf/tensor_data_base.HC` and parity tests in `tests/test_gguf_tensor_data_base.py` (WS2-04)\nIQ-050 todo :: Add offset-index integrity validator `GGUFValidateSortedTensorIndex` (permutation+range checks) in `src/gguf/tensor_data_base.HC` with adversarial host parity tests (WS2-04)\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
